843
01:40:13,990 --> 01:40:16,867
It's a fucking witch-hunt!

844
01:40:30,990 --> 01:40:34,823
And I'm calling in all debts.

845
01:40:34,989 --> 01:40:36,502
Well...

846
01:40:38,030 --> 01:40:40,908
We can't pay but...
but if you just maybe give us some...

847
01:40:41,070 --> 01:40:45,349
I'm not giving anything!
No more fucking favours!

848
01:40:47,791 --> 01:40:51,260
Now you're not leaving here,
till you pay me back.

849
01:40:53,791 --> 01:40:57,385
And if you can't pay me back,
you're not leaving at all.

850
01:41:00,791 --> 01:41:02,782
We're really gonna die.

851
01:41:02,951 --> 01:41:06,784
Now, Plugger here tells me
you were a journalist.

852
01:41:06,950 --> 01:41:10,023
<i>Uh, yeah. Yeah, rock critic
for Hot Press.</i>

853
01:41:10,191 --> 01:41:11,510
A few bits for the school mag.

854
01:41:11,671 --> 01:41:13,468
I tell you, my Pulitzer Prize
is still a ways off, I...

855
01:41:13,631 --> 01:41:16,191
Shut up, Neil. Neil's just
being modest, Mr. Machin.

856
01:41:16,352 --> 01:41:17,705
He's a great writer.
He's brilliant.

857
01:41:17,872 --> 01:41:19,988
It's his calling.
Isn't that right, Neil?

858
01:41:23,231 --> 01:41:25,462
Yeah. Yeah.

859
01:41:25,632 --> 01:41:28,384
My calling. You need someone
with press credentials.

860
01:41:28,551 --> 01:41:31,019
Someone to tell your side of the story.
Set the record straight.

861
01:41:31,191 --> 01:41:32,625
The man behind the myth,
kind of thing.

862
01:41:32,792 --> 01:41:35,226
Without bias, without agenda.

863
01:41:39,711 --> 01:41:41,862
Oh, there's an agenda, all right.

864
01:41:43,392 --> 01:41:45,383
I assume you want to live?

865
01:41:47,192 --> 01:41:49,753
OK. So you do this thing for me.
You write my story,

866
01:41:49,913 --> 01:41:52,984
you sell it to the papers
and you pay me back every penny.

867
01:41:53,152 --> 01:41:55,905
You can ask me anything you like.
But you stay here and you write

868
01:41:56,073 --> 01:41:58,143
till you're finished and it better be
good enough to publish.

869
01:41:58,313 --> 01:41:59,826
Hang on.
We can't stay here.

870
01:41:59,992 --> 01:42:01,471
Like we said,
we've got this big gig on...

871
01:42:01,632 --> 01:42:04,227
You're not going anywhere,
you daft bollock.

872
01:42:04,393 --> 01:42:07,510
Either of you.
You can sharpen his pencils.

873
01:42:07,673 --> 01:42:09,742
- [typewriter clacking]
- [dog barks]

874
01:42:14,633 --> 01:42:16,510
- Come on.
- Will you stop your pacing?

875
01:42:16,673 --> 01:42:19,107
I can't. We're supposed to be
sound checking right now.

876
01:42:19,273 --> 01:42:21,834
You were the one that convinced him
this was such a great idea.

877
01:42:21,994 --> 01:42:25,952
In what fucking universe
is this my fault?

878
01:42:26,113 --> 01:42:29,151
You have a gift.
Never mind the pop star bollocks.

879
01:42:29,314 --> 01:42:32,988
You could be the next James Joyce.
